article.headline: New Orleans 93, SE Oklahoma State 75
article.story:
TYLER, Texas (AP) -- Wayne Williams scored 34 points to lead New
Orleans to a 93-75 victory over Southeastern Oklahoma on Thursday
night.

Williams hit 15-of-21 from the field, including 3-of-4 from
3-point range. James Parlow and Earnest Daney added 15 points each
for New Orleans (2-4). Shawn Malloy scored 12 points.

Eric Babers led Southeastern Oklahoma with 29 points and Jason
Stampley added 16. Stephen Harrell scored 12 points.

New Orleans led 46-33 at the half.
